HEADWORD: Double-ender
<hw>Dou"ble-end"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A vessel capable of moving in either direction,
having bow and rudder at each end.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<fld>(Railroad)</fld> <def>A locomotive with pilot at each end.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

